        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 25 at 4:57PM PDT by NWS Sacramento CA</headline>
        <description>At 456 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Fall River Mills, or 10 miles southeast of Dana, moving southeast at
15 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pittville, Fall River Mills, and Mcarthur.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
